comments.body:
> Using subprocesses in python2 and python3, you will see python3 return things as bytes and python2 as strings as a simple example.

This really seems something outside the scope of skopeo itself - also, while I would have loved a well-integrated IPC, even D-BUS, that really seems a lot of work when instead we could add more strong parsing on subprocess return(s) in both python versions.

@baude am I missing something saying that it can be up to atomic to have a stronger parsing around subprocess returns?

> not language-neutral;

C bindings work for various languages, not just C: python, ruby, node, and Java.

[Varlink API](https://varlink.org/) does look like a better option though.
